   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-a" mid="102" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="72"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>And... I hope you don't tell the Bao Hybrids about this.<BR>According to what I found out from the notes, the meteor core fragment is... really small.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-b" mid="103" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="73"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>It's small? </FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-c" mid="104" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="74"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>Even if you manage to get the meteor core fragment, it will be <FONT color=#a94407>just enough to cure one person</FONT>. <BR>Suriya firmly believes that the Natives can turn into humans by cleansing the poison but that's practically impossible with such a small amount of the fragment.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-d" mid="105" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="75"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>By the way... there's something Master Karacule didn't want me to tell Suriya about... The hybrids don't have poison in their bodies anymore.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-e" mid="106" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="76"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>Their ears and tails appeared due to the poison but it's a physical change that was formed when the body cured itself from poison like how chickenpox leaves pockmarks. It's not that the hybrids have ears and tails because of the poison remaining in their bodies. So since the Natives already don't have poison in them, they will still look the same even when they are cleansed.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-f" mid="107" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="77"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Why don't you tell Suriya about it? He's an idiot.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-1-g" mid="108" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="78"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>He's staking everything on the power of the meteor core fragment so he would definitely give up on the Bao Hybrids if he finds out about this. That's why master told me not to tell him about it yet. She said maybe we can find other ways to get rid of the ears and tails when we finished analysing the notes so I didn't tell him about it.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n707_sidel-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Sidel.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n707_sidel-2" mid="109" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="79"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>But it was clearly stated in the notes how you could be cured. Let's make a purification device for the contaminated Natives first so that we can use it immediately when we get the meteor core fragment!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
